\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 John turned towards her, put his elbow up on the railing and kind of slumped into his shoulder like an apathetic miff before asking, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Deborah, what do you care about?\u8221\'94 His eyes narrowed, but not too seriously. Deborah couldn\u8217\'92t imagine his serious look could possible be. Maybe this is it. She took a moment to study his stare, trying to figure out if he knew who she was and what she was doing in Shreveport. }
