\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Drink, or a dance?\u8221\'94, she asked.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Well\u8230\'85 since I\u8217\'92ve not danced before I think it\u8217\'92s best if-\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Great. Drinks first though.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 With that, Deborah led a dazed but leering Peter back to the bar. At first he barely held on, but she could literally feel him warming up to the idea, and she hoped that another scotch, a fresh martini, and her company might convince him to settle into it. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Guided by the music, she and John made their way back down to the first deck, where the bodies were moving a little more slowly than before. Deborah hunched over her drink slightly as she sashayed across the deck, eager not to spill a drop amidst all of the close elbows and shoulders. After a few close calls, she raised the glass to her lips to down half of it, then set it on one of the wooden sills bolted into the wall. John took her hand, and then they danced.}
