\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Deborah expected to stumble into an uncomfortably practical arrangement, something like a fold-out cot with barely enough space for one person to sit, let alone enough for two to get involved. Instead there was a comfy looking twin-sized bed with an oaken frame that fit so perfectly flush to each wall that it had to have been custom made, and it was the only piece of furniture in the room because there wasn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t enough space for anything else. John could barely close the door behind him.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Deborah felt, again, like she had stumbled into a dream, only this time it was someone else's - whoever had originally converted this storage space into the ideal spot for a lazy afternoon nap.  It wasn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t so great for evening sex, but it was certainly better than an airplane toilet. And I can still hear the voices outside. She thought that would be what made this special, that they were risking something, that they were so thinly stretching the boundary between their public and private lives.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I hope that window opens up,\u8221\'94 John said as he dabbed a few beads of sweat from his brow with his handkerchief. It was a warm night, and the room lacked air conditioning. He promptly took off his shoes and jacket, put his phone on top, jumped onto the bed, scootched his way up to the window, and pried it open. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \tab \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Better?\u8221\'94, Deborah asked.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \tab The view overlooked the boat\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s red-metal water wheel, and outside cool air matched the cool evening light to synesthetic effect, as if the river\u8217\'92s breeze were casting light into the room, a pale and purplish turkish blue. Deborah kicked off her boots and jumped onto the bed, then let out a little squeal of delight as her thighs brushed up against the cool cotton sheets. It made her want to jump out of her clothes. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93How can you lay there like that?\u8221\'94, she asked. Jake had propped himself up with pillows, and was content to just let the wind cool the back of his neck. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93What do you mean?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93In that suit,\u8221\'94 Deborah noted as she unbuttoned her blouse. \u8220\'93I would be going mad.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I loosened my tie.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93But it\u8217\'92s -\u8221\'94 she paused to pull her blouse free over her head. \u8220\'93It\u8217\'92s the sheets, they\u8217\'92re nice and cool.\u8221\'94}
