\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Deborah hated seeing schadenfreude. It gave her the sinking feeling that happiness always comes into the world with an equal and opposite amount of unhappiness. She was afraid that \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8216\'91Balance\u8217\'92, capital-B, was the unifying theme of the cosmos, because it was even written into the very structure of the vacuum. When brushing up on Beksinski\u8217\'92s tech, she\u8217\'92d read that the charge of each positive particle that randomly pops into existence is negated by an anti-particle that randomly pops into existence right alongside it. She could imagine that basic principle propagating itself all the way up through the world of atoms to molecules to human moments, that happiness causes sadness somewhere just like light casts shadows.}
