\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Effective Sept. 16, 2011, any patent issued on or after that date is subject to the defense that an alleged infringer "commercially used\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94 the subject matter of the patent in the U.S. more than one year prior to the earlier of the filing date of the patent or the date the claimed invention was publicly disclosed.The expanded defense covers all patent-eligible subject matter used in a manufacturing or other commercial process.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 The Act expands the definition of \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93commercial use\u8221\'94 to include:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Premarketing regulatory review, when the safety or efficacy of the subject matter is established}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Use by a nonprofit entity whose intended beneficiary is the public}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Commercially used, abandoned and then used again technology cannot claim the benefit of the earlier use.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Also, there is a significant \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93University Exception\u8221\'94: the defense does not apply if the patented invention was \u8220\'93made, owned or subject to an obligation of assignment to an institution of higher education\u8221\'94 or to an affiliated technology transfer organization. Thus, if the technology is in a field where university research is active, it remains subject to potential jeopardy.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Although the defense is personal to the entity that performed or directed performance of the \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93commercial use,\u8221\'94 it may also be asserted by any entity that controls, is controlled by or under common control with the original entity. The defense is also transferable as part of a good-faith transfer with the whole line of business to which the defense relates.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Not a litigator, but typically during litigation there is a "discovery phase."  The other party can request you provide the details of your process, even though it is a trade secret.  If the request is approved by a judge, your process will be reviewed by a third, independent party, which promises confidentiality. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 In one well known case, inventors approached a large company about licensing technology before their patent had been issued. These smart inventors had the good sense to treat their as yet unpatented technology as a trade secret, and required the company to sign a nondisclosure agreement.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 After learning about the technology the large company told the inventors it wasn't interested, but subsequently incorporated the technology into the company product line without telling or compensating the inventors. Once the patent had issued the inventors sued for both patent infringement and trade secret misappropriation.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Ultimately the courts found the inventors' patent to be invalid, but upheld the trade secret misappropriation claim. The result was that the inventors received a multimillion dollar judgment they would have otherwise not obtained had they failed to treat their invention as a trade secret when disclosing it to the large company.}
